programme.title: General Hospital
programme.desc: The classic Gloria Monty soap charting the trials of Port Charles' medical center. Even daytime naysayers tuned in to see the celebrated nuptials of supercouple Luke and Laura, who scored covers of both Time and Newsweek during the same month. Over time, the series flirted with sci-fi, sexy aliens, adventurous location shoots and a late '90s mafia madness. It debuted on April Fools' Day 1963 and spun off the gothic guilty pleasure that was 'Port Charles' (which was canceled in 2003). (New).

programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about a mentally unstable news anchor who, after being told he's to be fired, becomes a media superstar when he begins delivering nightly rants and threatens an on-air suicide for his final broadcast. Paddy Chayevsky's script won an Oscar for Best Original Screenplay; Peter Firth received a posthumous Best Actor award as the unhinged newsman; and Faye Dunaway won Best Actress as a scheming network exec. (Repeat).

programme.title: Tom Horn
programme.desc: Steve McQueen portrays the legendary frontiersman caught up in a range war. Linda Evans, Richard Farnsworth. Joe: Billy Green Bush. Sam: Slim Pickens. Stable Hand: Elisha Cook. William Wiard directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Cincinnati Kid
programme.desc: A young poker player hustles in 1930s New Orleans. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Yellow Sky
programme.desc: When a band of outlaws hiding out in a ghost town learn that there is gold in the area, they plan to kill off the only inhabitant and claim it for themselves, but their leader opposes the plan. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Man in the Gray Flannel Suit
programme.desc: The personal and professional problems of a businessman. Gregory Peck, Jennifer Jones, Fredric March, Marisa Pavan. Gardella: Keenan Wynn. Bernstein: Lee J. Cobb. Mrs. Hopkins: Ann Harding. Nunnally Johnson directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Gentleman's Agreement
programme.desc: This Best Picture winner is about the experiences of a journalist who pretends to be Jewish to gather data for an exposé on anti-Semitism, and the hatred he is subjected to that takes its toll on his personal life. Elia Kazan won a Best Director Oscar and Celeste Holm received the award for Best Supporting Actress. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Grapes of Wrath
programme.desc: John Ford's powerful adaptation of the John Steinbeck classic about a destitute farm family migrating from Dust Bowl Oklahoma to "the promised land," California, during the Great Depression. Henry Fonda stars and Jane Darwell won a Supporting Actress Oscar as Ma Joad, the soft-spoken, determined matriarch of the clan. Ford won for his directing. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: No Way Out
programme.desc: A bigoted hoodlum is treated by a black intern. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Blackboard Jungle
programme.desc: An early film study of teens gone wild chronicles the efforts of an idealistic and dedicated teacher trying to cope with his classroom full of incorrigibles, including knife-wielding punks, in an urban high school. The film launched Bill Haley & the Comets' rock-and-roll anthem "Rock Around the Clock." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Edge of the City
programme.desc: An army deserter gets a job on the New York City waterfront, where he befriends a black dockworker and butts heads with a corrupt, racist union boss. Martin Ritt's first directorial effort was written by Robert Alan Aurthur, who adapted his television play "A Man Is Ten Feet Tall." Sidney Poitier reprises his role from the TV drama. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Little Nikita
programme.desc: Sidney Poitier plays an FBI agent who discovers that the parents of a teen (River Phoenix) are Soviet spies. Grant: Richard Jenkins. Elizabeth: Caroline Kava. Karpov: Richard Bradford. Scuba: Richard Lynch. Verna: Loretta Devine. Directed by Richard Benjamin. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Brian's Song
programme.desc: A look at the special relationship between Gale Sayers and Brian Piccolo, both star players for the Chicago Bears. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Monster's Ball
programme.desc: Halle Berry's Oscar-winning performance highlights this wrenching tale about racism, redemption and the power of love. She plays a poor Southern waitress who falls for a prison guard (Billy Bob Thornton) following the execution of her husband (played by rapper Sean Combs). Peter Boyle, Heath Ledger.(n)

programme.title: An Unfinished Life
programme.desc: A single mother tries to reconcile with her estranged former father-in-law, who blames her for the death of his son. Robert Redford, Jennifer Lopez and Morgan Freeman star in this powerful and heartwarming story of redemption. Josh Lucas, Damian Lewis, Camryn Manheim. Directed by Lasse Hallstrom. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Morituri
programme.desc: In this WWII spy story, a German deserter is coerced by a British Intelligence officer to impersonate a Gestapo official in order to get aboard a German blockade runner that is carrying a valuable rubber cargo from the Orient. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Reward
programme.desc: A crash-landed crop-duster betrays a fugitive and his girlfriend to Mexican bounty hunters. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Jubal
programme.desc: A young drifter finds trouble on a large ranch. Well-acted. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Warlock
programme.desc: A gunman is hired to rid a town of outlaws. Richard Widmark, Henry Fonda, Anthony Quinn. Jessie: Dolores Michaels. Lilly: Dorothy Malone. Edward Dmytryk directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Dog Day Afternoon
programme.desc: A bank robbery in Brooklyn goes wrong and evolves into a protracted hostage situation, turning the plan's mastermind into a media celebrity and the event into a media circus. Based on a true story. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Principal
programme.desc: A high-school teacher with a bad record is transferred to a gang-dominated school, as principal. He becomes the enemy of a sadistic gang leader as he tries cleaning up the school, and must team up with the head of security to end the gan leader's reign. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Get Carter
programme.desc: A ruthless hood suspects his brother's supposedly accidental death was no accident, and sniffs out the trail of lies and deceit with bloody consequences. (Repeat).(n)
